Subject: RE: [VB] Shift rod help!

The bus is a 65 DC, sorry for the poor pre-info :) I found the nub that
the DPO left me where the bolt should have been. I drilled it out and
worked it for about an hour and it came loose. Stuff like this is par
for the course with this bus. You should see the "custom" u-bolt that
was welded to the bushing carrier to hold the front shift rod up. All is
back in place now and the shifter feels really good! Thanks for the
quick reply!!!
TJ

